fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
A functor E\xrightarrow {L} F preserves a left Kan
extension (\operatorname *{Lan}_K F, \eta ) if 




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
  \usetikzlibrary{shapes.geometric}
  \usetikzlibrary{calc}
  \usetikzlibrary{matrix}
  \usetikzlibrary{decorations.markings}

  \tikzset{
    % basics
    square/.style={draw, regular polygon, regular polygon sides=4},
    triangle/.style={draw, regular polygon, regular polygon sides=3},
  }

  \tikzset{
    % string diagrams
    state/.style={triangle, shape border rotate=180, anchor=north},
    costate/.style={triangle, anchor=south},
    morphism/.style={draw, rectangle},
    over/.style={
      draw=white,
      double=black,
      % default is .4pt
      line width=1.2pt,
      double distance=.4pt,
      text=black
    },
  }

  \tikzset{ 
    % tables
    % https://tikz.net/tikz-table/
    table/.style={
        matrix of nodes,
        row sep=-\pgflinewidth,
        column sep=-\pgflinewidth,
        nodes={
            rectangle,
            draw=black,
            align=center
        },
        minimum height=1.5em,
        text depth=0.5ex,
        text height=2ex,
        nodes in empty cells,
%%
        every even row/.style={
            nodes={fill=gray!20}
        },
        column 1/.style={
            nodes={font=\bfseries}
        },
        row 1/.style={
            nodes={
                fill=black,
                text=white,
                font=\bfseries
            }
        }
    }
  }


  \begin {tikzcd}
    C\ar [rr, "F", ""' {name=F}]\ar [dr, "K"'] && E\ar [r, "L"] & F\\
    & D\ar [ur, "\operatorname *{Lan}_K F"']
    \ar [from=F, to=2-2, Rightarrow, "\eta "]
  \end {tikzcd}$\cong $
  \begin {tikzcd}
    C\ar [r, "F"]\ar [dr, "K"'] & E\ar [r, "L"] & F\\
    & D\ar [ur, "\operatorname *{Lan}_K LF"']
    \ar [from=1-2, to=2-2, Rightarrow]
  \end {tikzcd},


 i.e. if the Kan extension of LF along K is naturally
isomorphic to the whiskered composite of \eta  by L.

The category of presheaves \hat {C} is the free
cocompletion of C, in an appropriately weak 2-categorical sense. In
particular, for every functor C\xrightarrow {F} E with E cocomplete, there exists,
uniquely up to unique isomorphism, a cocontinuous functor
\hat {C}\to  E that extends the Yoneda embedding of C: 




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
  \usetikzlibrary{shapes.geometric}
  \usetikzlibrary{calc}
  \usetikzlibrary{matrix}
  \usetikzlibrary{decorations.markings}

