    \begin {tikzcd}
      \operatorname {Sub}(x)\ar [d, "f^*"']\ar [r, "\chi "] & C(x, \Omega )\ar [d, "{C(f, \Omega )}"]\\
      \operatorname {Sub}(y)\ar [r, "\chi "'] & C(y, \Omega )
    \end {tikzcd}


 commutes. (There is some notational overload here: the map C(f, \Omega )
  acts on maps x\to \Omega  by pre-composition with f; we generally also
  write this f^*. This theorem justifies the overloaded notation.)
  In particular, we need to show, for any subobject s\hookrightarrow  x, the equality
  y\xrightarrow {f}x\xrightarrow {\chi _s} \Omega  = \chi _{f^*s}. By definition of \chi _s and
  f^*s, we have the diagram 




