     \end {tikzcd} \quad $=$\quad  \begin {tikzcd}
       x\ar [r, "f"]\ar [d, equals]\ar [dr, phantom, "\lrcorner ", very near start] & \omega \ar [d, hook, "\top "] \\
       x\ar [r, "\top  f"'] & \Omega \makebox [0pt][l]{.}
     \end {tikzcd}


 Thus \top  f classifies 1_x, so that f is unique since \top  is
   monic and (by the previous paragraph) characteristic maps are unique.

A braided monoidal category is a monoidal category C
equipped with a braiding natural isomorphism x\otimes  y\xrightarrow {\gamma _{xy}} y\otimes  x satisfying the coherence
conditions entailed by commutativity of: 




