 be an adjunction. Let J\xrightarrow {K} D be a
  diagram and \operatorname *{lim} K\xrightarrow {\lambda _j} K_j be a limiting
  cone over K. We show that the cone G\operatorname *{lim} K\xrightarrow {G\lambda _j}   GK_j is in fact a limiting cone over GK. We need the following two
  observations:

adjunctions lift to functor categories;

the constant diagram functor commutes with functors.

The comma category c\downarrow  G has as objects pairs (d\in  D,   c\xrightarrow {f} Gd\in  C) and as maps maps d\xrightarrow {g} d'\in  D making the triangle 




